## Target audience and positioning decision

The strongest primary audience for Aviera is **young male athletes and performance-driven lifters**, especially those between roughly 22 and 35 who care about pumps, strength, recovery, sleep quality, hydration, and stack optimization. Glanbia’s 2025 active-adult trends note that active consumers prioritize hydration, energy, protein, and micronutrients while using digital tools and online resources to guide nutrition choices.[1] A recent systematic review in *Frontiers in Nutrition* also found high supplement use among athletes and supported individualized, evidence-based supplementation rather than generic protocols.[2] Additional sports-nutrition literature shows the field is moving toward more personalized and precision-oriented guidance.[3]

This audience fits the current product catalog unusually well. Flow State X maps to pump and blood-flow goals. Nitric Shock maps to pre-workout intent. Creatine maps to broad performance and education demand. Magnesium Glycinate maps to recovery and sleep. Hydration powder maps to electrolyte and endurance support. The quiz provides the differentiation layer, but the acquisition layer should still be built around the high-demand categories.

| Audience tier | Description | Core needs | Primary messages |
|---|---|---|---|
| Primary | Men 22 to 35 who lift, hybrid train, or chase physique and performance outcomes | Better training performance, pumps, recovery, hydration, sleep, convenient stack guidance | Personalized stacks without guesswork; evidence-aware performance support |
| Secondary | Active adults seeking clean, premium supplementation | Better daily energy, sleep, hydration, foundational support | Premium supplements guided by a tailored recommendation flow |
| Tertiary | Supplement-curious shoppers comparing clean or stimulant-sensitive options | Fewer jitters, simpler choices, trustworthy education | Clear formulas, transparent labels, beginner-friendly guidance |

