### Core technical findings

The most urgent technical issue is the absence of valid crawl-control and discovery files. A public request to `https://avierafit.com/robots.txt` and `https://avierafit.com/sitemap.xml` resolved to 404 pages during the audit.[13] [14] The root domain does properly redirect to `www.avierafit.com`, which is fine, but the indexing layer still needs to be completed.[12]

The second major issue is metadata duplication. The extracted HTML summary indicates that the homepage, shop page, news page, and several product pages share the same broad title and meta description. This weakens relevance for non-branded queries and makes it harder for search engines to understand page-level intent.

The third issue is limited machine-readable trust context. The current pages show persuasive human copy, but there is insufficient structured evidence for AI systems to cite with confidence. That includes missing or limited Product schema, FAQ schema, Organization schema, and HowTo schema.

