### Canonicals, hreflang, and redirects

Aviera does not currently need hreflang because the audited site appears to target a single English-language U.S. audience. If internationalization is added later, hreflang should only be deployed when there are genuinely localized alternates. The main redirect requirement today is to preserve the non-`www` to `www` redirect and to keep future blog URL conventions stable.

| URL rule | Recommendation |
|---|---|
| `https://avierafit.com/*` | 301 redirect to `https://www.avierafit.com/*` |
| Legacy product name URLs if renamed | 301 old URL to new category-optimized URL |
| Tracking parameter variants | Canonicalize to clean URL |
| Dashboard/account routes | Consider `noindex, nofollow` if user-specific |

